OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: MOAT SURROUNDING FORT PULASKI NM
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION IS LOCATED ON THE FORT PULASKI; GA.S.C. 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  THIS SITE IS IN FORT PULSKI NATIONAL MONUMENT AND IS LOCATED ON THE MOAT WHICH SURROUNDS THE FORT.  WATER QUALITY HAS BEEN MONITORED AT THIS STATION ON A MONTHLY BASIS SINCE JANUARY 1994 AS PART OF A PROGRAM DESIGNED TO MEASURE NUTRIENT AND SALINITY LEVELS AND TO ASSESS THE POTENTIAL FOR ALGAL BLOOMS AND DETERIORATION OF THE FORT'S BRICK MASONRY.  SAMPLES ARE TYPICALLY COLLECTED THE LAST WEEK OF THE MONTH ALTHOUGH EXACT SAMPLE DATES ARE NOT RECORDED.  PARAMETERS MONITORED FOR THIS PROGRAM INCLUDE WATER TEMPERATURE; MONTHLY RAIN; SALINITY; PH; D.O.; NITRATE; NITRITE; AND FECAL COLIFORM.  FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT PARK RANGER; FORT PULASKI NATIONAL MONUMENT; U.S. HIGHWAY 80 EAST; P.O. BOX 30757; SAVANNAH; GA 314100757.  (TEL. 912 7865787).  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY ERIC JANNEY OF THE NPS; WATER RESOURCES DIVISION; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE; SUITE 250; FT. COLLINS; CO 80525.  (TEL. 970 2253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /CANAL/TYPA/AMBNT

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: John Ward Creek Downstream at KEMO Boundary
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located where John Ward Creek intersects the western boundary of Kennesaw Mountain National Battlefield Park.  The station can be found on the Marietta GA 7.5' U.S. Geological Survey quadrangle. Station is one of four water quality monitoring stations maintained by Kennesaw Mountain National Battlefield to detect changes in baseline water quality conditions over time.  This stream begins in rapidly developing Marietta Georgia before traverse the park.  Data collection began in 1994 and was ongoing as of 1999.  Park staff collect the field data and take samples to the Cobb County Water Lab for bacteriological analysis and to the USGS Georgia District for analyses of the other parameters.  Supervised volunteers from North Cobb High School have collected SQS biological data at this station.  Kennesaw Mountain NBP contact is Rich Biurgren; 900 Kennesaw Mtn. Dr.; Kennesaw GA 30152 (tel. 7704274686).  Data processed and uploaded to STORET by Dean Tucker; NPS Water Resources Division (tel. 9702253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

MonitoringLocationName: East Fork Little River
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This site is accessed from state road 117 below the bridge.  It is a narrow part of the river with sand and bedrock substrate.  This site is located in Chattooga County, Georgia.  This site is important because of the many uses within this sub-watershed.  Domestic development, agriculture, clear-cutting, and reclaimed strip mines are prevalent throughout the area.  Access is easy and safe in all conditions.
